name: Mets
summary: The New York Mets' remarkable season concluded with a Game 6 loss to the Los Angeles Dodgers in the National League Championship Series (NLCS). The Mets' magical run ended as they bowed to the Dodgers' dominance. In Game 2, the Mets' Starling Marte scored a home run to halt the Dodgers' scoreless streak and tie the NLCS 1-1. However, in a surprising turn of events, Edwin Diaz and the Mets' bullpen allowed a late-inning comeback in Game 5, putting the team on the brink of elimination. The Mets' bullpen, known as the "savages," rallied to keep the NLCS alive. Despite an early lead in Game 6, the Mets fell to the Dodgers, ending their playoff journey and marking the Dodgers' advancement to the World Series against the New York Yankees.
